Friday. September IE, ”57
 
IN THE BEGINNING . . .
Last December set the president, and now both the administration and the student
body are reading the results
of the turmoil which that inconclusive battle created. “Now
we must try again," is the
cry; challenge the states que;
go to the extreme to get results, action over reason, not
for the sake at, or in the service of reason, but for the sake
of action itself. What is the
cause of this annual battle-cry?
What is the end in View? What
are the real medications for so
acting? clearly not everyone
feels exactly the some way, or
has the same end in view, but
at the same time. a large number of people are willing to participate In a common action, or
common means to diverse ends,
How can this be?
The first confusion that must
he noted is one having to do
With ends, or what those people who have originally the
controversy really want. That
is, are the ends which are
sought broadbased enough to
warrant such every action, or are
they really too miniature to
be allowed to assume the
productions of principles
Worth fighting for? This
‘l‘Iistlncthn must be realized before any action whatsoever can
