Well. wells It seems that some people have been slightly upset
by some of my recent columns merely because my facts are ins
accurate,
For example, I said there would be two instead of three
referred this year which is incorrect. I also said the Smith press
beat the Clark press while, in truth, they never made it past midfield which can hardly be construct as nomination play.
in any case, I find this insightﬁcant as my journalistic month
Is, “It matters not whether you tell the truth, but whether what you
say makes good reading.” In the future 1 will try to be slightly
more accurate but don't go betting the family levels on the authenticity of my statements
Having looked at the I. M. football schedule [or this year, I
notice that the games will be played just a hop, step, and jump
from the center of the campus. All games, that is, With the election of those played on Stable Field which is a hop, step, and
amp, . . . and hop, . . . and lead, . r . and two giant steps, . . .
and eleven sponsor steps, . . . and four hundred and fifteen strikes,
. . The reason for this is that Mac Field is going to be turned
into an aboretum or something and therefore we must not treat
on it, This is about as possible as putting up Keep on the Grass
signs in a national park I worlds’t go so far as to say Stable
told is out of the way, but at the last game, four aboriginal tried
eat our footballr As a famous English poet once said (or was he
l'each?), “We’d deadly give up girls and meals /lr you'd give us
act our football fields.” or was he Persian? Chinese? , r .
 
