The cross country season
opens tomorrow with a dual of
three miles against joe. it is
scheduled to start at 11 aim.
at the Griiineli cmss country
course, which begins on the
Ward Field track, goes across
the soccer fields to the golf
course and back again.
Coach Obermlller expects his
carriers to have a fairly successful season if everyone stays
healthy. The team is led by
captain Doug gray with Bob
Asbille, Bob Grant and Spencer Clark mentioned as other
outstanding winners. Asbille is
a sophomore and the rest are
seniors Other members of the
squad include senior George
Potter, seniors Bruce Luecke
and Phil belong and sophomores Eric Thor, John gilbert,
Steve diesel, and Glen browsing.
A cross cﬂentry team race is
either three or four miles long.
The official variety distance is
four miles and the official
freshman distance is three
miles. A team consists of seven
winners with the top five {flashers on each team scoringl
The runner finishing first gets
one point, the second finished
gets two points and so our The
team with the lowest score
wins. Thus, the man running
fifth {or the learn is as essential to the team effort as
the number one man on the
squad.
Also running against (Joe tomorrow, but not included in
the scoring, will be the freshman team,
