By JOHN RA:
The change of suit preference
signal is a useful defensive signal which may give partner the
key to the defense of the contract It is used when one is
free to lead one of several
cards in a holding and one
wishes to direct partner to lead
one of two questionable suits.
In the following hand, after
the six of spaces opening lead,
the queen was played from
jimmy, which was taken by =
East's ace, as declared dropped ff,” prff" 332°“
the seven. Not looked by De- 4H p,“ p,“
player's raisecard, East re- Opening ind, leads six
turned the jack of spaces which
West buffer, West realized that East was free to lead any card in
his space holding and that the lead of the jack might be a change
of suit preference signal. Of the two suits other than trust (in this
case, diamonds and clubs), at high card signals partner to lead
the higher ranking of the two suits, while a low card signals the
lead of the lower ranking suit. East returned a diamond, the higher
ranking suit hoping that he found an entry to East’s hand. East
cached the ace and returned a space to defeat the contract
of course, before this convention is used it must be agreed tips
on by the partnership. The signal has wide application in no—trust
as well as trust contracts, and again is based upon two conditions: one must be able to lead any card in one’s holding and the
card must be recognized as such; and there can be only two suits
to be distinguished, a high card signature the higher ranking suit,
a low card signature the lower ranking suite
